  "pages": [
    {
      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "The board of public works is much\nperturbed because the city council at\nits last meeting referred to the board\nthe perplexing problem of vacating\npart of Main avenue west of the Mon\nroe street bridge to the Spokane Falls\nGas Light company.\n\n\nFriends of the proposed dedication\nmaintain that the city gets the best\nof the bargain, because in exchange\nfor deep chasm underneath the\nbridge it is given the triangle at the\nfoot of the bridge. which cost the gas\ncompany sS00S, and which could be\nused for pretty fountain or even\nfor the library building; is given a\nstone retaining wall that will cost\n$4,000; is given the cost of filling in\nthe street, and is enabled to save the\nexpense of keeping up the wooden\npart of the south end of the bridge.\n\n\nProperty holders along the avenue,\nOn the other hand, contend the city is\ngiving too much for the returns"
    }
  ]
